Bottom Line
Yes, for your stack, an application-layer firewall first is the best move.
A Linux nftables-style packet firewall inside kernel datapath would be much heavier than what you need now.

Why App-Layer First Fits TRUEOS

Your APIs are explicit: OpenTcpConnect, OpenTcpListen, SendUdp, SendTcp are clear intents, easier to enforce than raw packet parsing:
adapter.rs:469

Most of your network usage is client-style service code under r/net/cli, so egress policy gives immediate value:
